{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352354468,"sessionID":"ses_31bfd06f5ffeleRCi6uuMulALr","part":{"id":"prt_ce408fa5b0024th7vhnAe9wCaL","sessionID":"ses_31bfd06f5ffeleRCi6uuMulALr","messageID":"msg_ce408ee730012Je0g7zEXB9nRp","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement a feature to replace direct tmux usage with a multiplexer abstraction layer that supports both **dmux** (a Rust-based terminal multiplexer, preferred) and **tmux** (fallback). The system should auto-detect which is available, prefer dmux, and be configurable via `wombo.json`. tmux support must NOT be removed — it must remain as a fallback.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- **Feature branch:** `feature/dmux-migration` based on `main`\n- **Commit guidelines:** Use conventional commits (`feat(dmux-migration):`, `refactor(dmux-migration):`, etc.), commit after each logical unit, do NOT squash, do NOT push, do NOT modify `.features.yml`\n- **Constraints:** Must detect available multiplexer (dmux preferred, tmux fallback), must maintain all existing session management functionality, must be configurable via `wombo.json` (`agent.multiplexer` field)\n- **Forbidden:** Do not remove tmux support entirely\n- **Build verification:** Run `bun run build` at the end to verify everything works. Fix errors if build fails.\n- The multiplexer preference config field is `agent.multiplexer` with values: `\"auto\"` (default, prefer dmux), `\"dmux\"`, or `\"tmux\"`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- The codebase is a Bun/TypeScript project called \"wombo-combo\" — an AI agent orchestration system\n- tmux references are spread across ~12 files: `launcher.ts`, `tui.ts`, `cleanup.ts`, `abort.ts`, `launch.ts`, `resume.ts`, `retry.ts`, `init.ts`, `schema.ts`, `index.ts`, `config.ts`, `monitor.ts`\n- `launcher.ts` is the core file with all session management (create, list, kill sessions)\n- `tui.ts` has a `tmuxAttach()` method for attaching to sessions from the TUI\n- Backward-compatible aliases were created (`tmuxSessionExists`, `killTmuxSession`, etc.) pointing to the new `mux*` functions so existing consumers don't break\n- The config type `WomboConfig` has `agent.tmuxPrefix` (kept as-is for session naming prefix) and new `agent.multiplexer` field\n- `bun run typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`) passes cleanly after each change\n- dmux command-line interface is assumed to be compatible with tmux's CLI syntax (same flags: `-d`, `-s`, `-t`, `-c`, `-F`, etc.)\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed:\n1. ✅ **Created `src/lib/multiplexer.ts`** — Full abstraction layer with detection (`detectMultiplexer()`), caching, and unified API functions (`muxNewSession`, `muxHasSession`, `muxKillSession`, `muxListSessions`, `muxGetPanePid`, `muxLoadBuffer`, `muxPasteBuffer`, `muxSendKeys`, `muxAttach`, `muxDisplayName`, `muxAttachCommand`, `muxListCommand`)\n2. ✅ **Updated `src/config.ts`** — Added `MultiplexerPreference` import, `agent.multiplexer` field to `WomboConfig` interface, default value `\"auto\"` in `DEFAULT_CONFIG`\n3. ✅ **Refactored `src/lib/launcher.ts`** — Replaced all direct tmux calls with multiplexer abstraction. Added `killMuxSession`, `muxSessionExists`, `listMuxSessions`, `killAllMuxSessions`, `getMultiplexerName`. Kept backward-compatible aliases.\n4. ✅ **Updated `src/lib/tui.ts`** — Replaced `tmuxAttach()` with `muxAttach()`, uses `detectMultiplexer()` and abstraction functions\n5. ✅ **Updated `src/commands/cleanup.ts`** — Uses `killAllMuxSessions`, `getMultiplexerName`, `detectMultiplexer` + `muxListSessions` for dry-run\n6. ✅ **Updated `src/commands/abort.ts`** — Uses `killMuxSession`, `getMultiplexerName`, renamed `tmuxKilled` → `muxKilled`\n7. ✅ **Commits made (4 so far):**\n   - `feat(dmux-migration): add multiplexer abstraction layer and config`\n   - `refactor(dmux-migration): migrate launcher.ts to multiplexer abstraction`\n   - `refactor(dmux-migration): update TUI to use multiplexer abstraction`\n   - `refactor(dmux-migration): update cleanup and abort commands for multiplexer`\n\n### In Progress:\n8. 🔄 **Updating `launch.ts`, `resume.ts`, `retry.ts`, `init.ts`** — launch.ts and resume.ts and retry.ts have been edited but NOT yet committed. The user-facing messages have been updated to use `getMultiplexerName()` and `muxAttachCommand()`/`muxListCommand()` instead of hardcoded \"tmux\" strings.\n\n### Remaining:\n9. ⬜ **Update `src/commands/init.ts`** — Line 149 still says `\"tmux session prefix\"` in the prompt text; should mention it's for the multiplexer session prefix. Also need to add a prompt for the new `multiplexer` config field.\n10. ⬜ **Update `src/lib/schema.ts`** — Lines 130, 149, 208 reference \"tmux TUI mode\"; lines 218-219, 233 reference \"tmux sessions\". Update descriptions.\n11. ⬜ **Update `src/index.ts`** — Lines 329, 357 reference \"tmux\" in help text.\n12. ⬜ **Commit the in-progress changes** (launch.ts, resume.ts, retry.ts)\n13. ⬜ **Update `wombo.json`** — Add `\"multiplexer\": \"auto\"` to the agent section\n14. ⬜ **Run `bun run build`** to verify everything works. Fix any errors.\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n- **Created:** `src/lib/multiplexer.ts` — Core multiplexer abstraction layer\n- **Modified (committed):**\n  - `src/config.ts` — Added `multiplexer` field to WomboConfig\n  - `src/lib/launcher.ts` — Replaced all tmux calls with mux abstraction\n  - `src/lib/tui.ts` — Updated session attach/detection\n  - `src/commands/cleanup.ts` — Uses mux abstraction for session cleanup\n  - `src/commands/abort.ts` — Uses mux abstraction for session kill\n- **Modified (uncommitted, in progress):**\n  - `src/commands/launch.ts` — Updated messages and imports\n  - `src/commands/resume.ts` — Updated messages and imports\n  - `src/commands/retry.ts` — Updated messages and imports\n- **Still needs updating:**\n  - `src/commands/init.ts` — Prompt text for tmuxPrefix + add multiplexer prompt\n  - `src/lib/schema.ts` — CLI flag descriptions\n  - `src/index.ts` — Help text\n  - `wombo.json` — Add multiplexer field to project config","time":{"start":1773352354467,"end":1773352354467}}}
