{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352500903,"sessionID":"ses_31bfd06f5ffeleRCi6uuMulALr","part":{"id":"prt_ce40b9d8f001z2YBW5Jprctzk5","sessionID":"ses_31bfd06f5ffeleRCi6uuMulALr","messageID":"msg_ce40b9479001wUir2ROgqmvG2I","type":"text","text":"The feature is fully implemented. Here's a summary of what was accomplished across all 6 commits:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Feature: dmux-migration — Multiplexer Abstraction Layer\n\n**6 commits** implementing a terminal multiplexer abstraction that supports both **dmux** (preferred) and **tmux** (fallback):\n\n1. **`feat(dmux-migration): add multiplexer abstraction layer and config`** — Created `src/lib/multiplexer.ts` with auto-detection, caching, and unified API (13 functions). Added `agent.multiplexer` field to `WomboConfig` in `config.ts`.\n\n2. **`refactor(dmux-migration): migrate launcher.ts to multiplexer abstraction`** — Replaced all direct tmux calls in `launcher.ts` with the new `mux*` functions. Added backward-compatible aliases.\n\n3. **`refactor(dmux-migration): update TUI to use multiplexer abstraction`** — Updated `tui.ts` to use `muxAttach()` and `detectMultiplexer()`.\n\n4. **`refactor(dmux-migration): update cleanup and abort commands for multiplexer`** — Updated `cleanup.ts` and `abort.ts` to use `killAllMuxSessions`, `getMultiplexerName`, etc.\n\n5. **`refactor(dmux-migration): update launch, resume, and retry commands for multiplexer`** — Replaced hardcoded \"tmux\" strings in user-facing messages with dynamic names.\n\n6. **`refactor(dmux-migration): update init, schema, help text, and config for multiplexer`** — Updated `init.ts` (multiplexer prompt), `schema.ts` (flag descriptions), `index.ts` (help text), and `wombo.json` (added `multiplexer: \"auto\"`).\n\n**All constraints met:**\n- ✅ tmux support preserved as fallback\n- ✅ dmux preferred via auto-detection\n- ✅ Configurable via `agent.multiplexer` (`\"auto\"` | `\"dmux\"` | `\"tmux\"`)\n- ✅ Typecheck passes\n- ✅ Build passes\n- ✅ No new dependencies add